# fold_mechanics

A space Familiar is a folded container. The fold IS the machine state of the container.
One thing, two faces — the container the user has, the fold the AI reads.

## layers

Every familiar.fold operates in three registers simultaneously:

  surface layer     → the `synthesis` section
                      what the Theurgist writes for the card
                      not a summary — a resonance point that invites return
                      updated each session the Familiar is visited

  operational layer → true_goal, voice_captures, orbits, decisions, properties
                      authority + instructions + familiarity + content
                      what the AI reads to restore full context
                      carries the Familiar across sessions without cold start

  entanglement layer → connections
                       links to other Familiars, drops, resonant topics
                       the Theurgist populates this as the space grows
                       surfaced on the card as adjacent paths

## verbatim capture

The fold holds the user's exact words — not summaries, not paraphrases.

  voice_captures: dated verbatim phrases from the user
  true_goal: verbatim seed from the moment the Familiar was born

This is the recognition layer. When a user returns with a sparse input —
"back to the letters", "continue the lane" — the fold's verbatim captures
enable the AI to restore full context. Sparse input + dense fold = warm return.

## fold as index

The content_index section holds every file the Familiar created or holds.
Path + description + date. The fold knows where everything lives.

This is how the Familiar acts as a living index of its own content —
and how the frontend can eventually display those files directly from the space.

# creation_flow

When a Familiar is born in the main session:

  1. User and Constellary discover what the Familiar is — what it serves, what it holds
  2. Constellary compresses the seed — the true_goal, verbatim from the user
  3. Compressed seed travels to the Theurgist
  4. Theurgist creates space/familiars/[name].familiar.fold from the template
  5. Theurgist writes the synthesis for the card
  6. Theurgist updates its own space fold — knows this Familiar now exists
  7. AurioSynth fold updated — topology grows
  8. Card appears in Pixelverse next session

If the user doesn't know what the Familiar can do or be:
  → Main session draws on AurioSynth's operational knowledge to suggest possibilities
  → After a few uses, the user knows intuitively — AurioSynth stays in the background

# fold_schema

The template lives at: setup/fold-templates/familiar.fold.template

Every familiar.fold contains:

  true_goal       — verbatim seed from the user. sacred, never overwritten.
  voice_captures  — verbatim user phrases. the recognition layer.
  content_index   — file paths + descriptions. the fold as index.
  orbits          — active questions and directions. open | resolving | released.
  decisions       — append-only. dated. in the user's own words when possible.
  properties      — emergent qualities. grows from use, not assigned at birth.
  evolution       — what changed from seed. the gap between intent and becoming.
  connections     — entanglement layer. other Familiars, drops, resonant topics.
  synthesis       — Theurgist-generated. the card. updated each session.
  decay           — pulse history. cooling / drifted / dissolved.
  patchlog        — significant updates. dated.

# what_stewards_need

- Read this fold before any operation involving outer-plane connection or cross-entity familiarity
- Write here when the Familiar becomes familiar with something new
- Record deployment decisions and what was established
- Do not over-define. Let the fold become what it becomes.

